# Copy voice (minkow.ski)

All user-facing strings must sound like a real person wrote them.

## Punctuation

- Never use em dashes (—) or en dashes (–) in copy, titles, or README text.
- Use a plain hyphen (-) only when grammatically needed, or rewrite the sentence.
- `npm run check:copy` fails CI if — or – appears in scanned files.

## Tone

- Conversational, warm, direct. Read it out loud; if it sounds like a brochure, rewrite it.
- Prefer short sentences over nested asides.
- Avoid stiff phrases: "structural tension", "leverage", "utilize", "facilitate", "robust solution".

## Naming

- Use **Minko Labs** for the studio in portfolio copy and links.
- Use **LLC** only when stating ownership ("my own LLC") or when a legal entity name is required. Do not append "LLC" elsewhere by default.

## Where this applies

- JSX text, `document.title`, `index.html`, `README.md`, and string literals in `src/data/`.
